messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Files containing the handler implementations:
- app/Http/Controllers/Api/V1/MediaController.php

Explanation:
- routes/api.php registers the controller for the /v1/media resource (two apiResource() calls): one outside the auth middleware that exposes the index action, and one inside the auth middleware that exposes store and destroy.
- I searched the project for occurrences of "MediaController" and opened the matching file. The controller implementation is in app/Http/Controllers/Api/V1/MediaController.php and includes the index(Request $request) method (as well as store and destroy).
- The index implementation returns a paginated collection:
  MediaResource::collection(MediaLibrary::first()->media()->paginate($request->input('limit', 20)))
- No other files define App\Http\Controllers\Api\V1\MediaController@index; the controller methods are implemented only in the file listed above.
